The hypothetical alternative release scenario for this facility is described as a pipe leak located in the compressor room of the facility.  This model is based upon the release of 626 pounds of anhydrous ammonia over a 10 minute period. Using a variety of factors, such as extreme and unlikely weather conditions, ammonia would travel a theoretical distance before dispersing.  Based upon the model, that distance could be up to 0.19 miles.  However, industry experts consider this hypothetical scenario to be unlikely for the following reasons:

- The weather conditions which were used for this scenario are unlikely to occur;
- Pressure safety valves limit operating pressures;
- Industry standards were followed for the manufacture and quality control of piping;
- There is a preventative maintenacne program in place to maintain the on-going integrity;
- Emergency stop buttons are located in areas outside of potential expsoure areas.

Continual Safety Updates

The facility strives for continual safety improvement.  Some areas of updates in the future shall include continued training for new employees and contractors and working with the Brown County Hazardous Response Team for emergency preparedness purposes (touring the facility and familiarizing themselves with the layout and configuration of the facility and the refrigeration process).
